-- NAB Reaches Deal to Sell Axa Asia's North Platform to IOOF, Herald Reports
-- Ben Sharples
-- 2010-07-22T20:57:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-22/nab-reaches-deal-to-sell-axa-asia-s-north-platform-to-ioof-herald-reports.html

          
          
             National Australia Bank Ltd. has
reached a deal to sell one of Axa Asia Pacific Holdings Ltd.’s
assets to IOOF Holdings Ltd. as it tries to gain regulatory
approval to purchase the investment manager, the Sydney Morning
Herald reported, without saying where it got the information.
The Melbourne-based bank is seeking to to offload Axa Asia
Pacific’s North platform, an Internet portal offering investment
and pension products, the newspaper said.  
